comments: Melton (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on Harris (BKN) as Harris fumbles away the entry pass.
Melton (MEM) cleanly blocks the jump shot attempt by Harris (BKN) and any ensuing contact to the hand/arm is considered incidental.

Green (BKN) slightly extends his arms out and some contact occurs to Anderson's (MEM) back as he tries to establish himself in a legal screening position.  The contact results in Anderson bumping into Shamet (BKN), but Shamet is able to play through the marginal contact and maintain a legal defensive position.
Harris (BKN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Harris (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Clarke's (MEM) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Clarke (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Shamet's (BKN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
At the end of the drive, Melton (MEM) and Clarke (MEM) maintain legal guarding positions on LeVert (BKN) as he makes an errant pass.
Harris (BKN) commits a take foul on Jones (MEM).
LeVert (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Anderson (MEM) and a timeout is granted prior to the ball being tied up.
The ball is not inbounded within five seconds.
During the inbound, LeVert (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Jones (MEM) off ball.
During the inbound, Luwawu-Cabarrot (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Allen (MEM) off ball.
Anderson (MEM) makes contact to LeVert's (BKN) body on the drive that affects his SQBR.
During the inbound, Brooks (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on LeVert (BKN) off ball and cleanly deflects the pass out of bounds.
During the screen, LeVert (BKN) comes to a stop and Brooks (MEM) makes marginal contact with him that does not dislodge him from his position.
Harris (BKN) could be deemed to be in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Shamet (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Allen (MEM) after he receives the inbound pass.
LeVert (BKN) commits a take foul on Bane (MEM).
During the inbound, Dieng (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on Luwawu-Cabarrot (BKN) and cleanly steals the errant pass.
